HEADWORD: Zoonite
<hw>Zo"o*nite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>One of the segments of the body of an articulate
animal.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the theoretic transverse
divisions of any segmented animal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

